There's currently a _serious_ design flaw in the client:
- the GUI is _required_ in order to handle mute/solo settings
- CClient doesn't hold a channel "fader" level - it just communicates the server mixer level required
- "mute" and "solo" need to know the level before it was set to zero, to restore it
- this is currently done by reading the GUI widget value!!
- this _breaks_ things like the MIDI control of mute/solo (and any other remote control ideas)
- there are various other things where the client design needs addressing (much of the mixer board doesn't use CClient values)


